Parents/Guardians:
It was brought to Woodland Teachers and Administration attention that there was a message saying that YouTube videos were "hacked" and could display inappropriate images to students that are learning remotely.

Woodland Staff identified that the actual "hack" is occurring on a different site and not YouTube. Woodland Teachers will be checking the safety of their links and have been briefed on how to check for appropriate and reputable sources to ensure student safety.

If you have any questions regarding this matter please feel free to reach out to administration at (815) 672-5974 or email Mr. Burcenski at burcenskij@woodland5.net.

Tomorrow starts National Read Across America WEEK. Take note how you can celebrate with Woodland on these dress up days!

Monday is Dr. Seuss Day - Wear silly socks!

Tuesday is Eric Carle Day - Make sure your wear the correct color so Brown Bear sees you!

Wednesday is Jan Brett Day - We don't expect people to wear socks on their heads, but you can wear a hat to school today!

Thursday is Amy Logan Day - Amy Logan will be visiting Woodland! Amy knows that superheroes make the world a better place. We ALL have that power. Wear a cape to school and lets get reading! Thank you to the Woodland PTO for getting Amy Logan to attend!

Friday is Anna Dewdney Day - For the 11:30 dismissal day, students should wear the pajamas so the can relax for a Read-a-thon!

post_text:
Streator and Woodland High School Youth Softball Camp 2020.

When: Saturday March 21, 2020
Where: SHS “Pops” Dale Gym

1 Session Only: Grades 1-8 (9:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.) Check in begins at 8:45 a.m. Participants will be broken into groups based on grade level.

Cost: $25 per camper ($15 per additional sibling)

Each camper that registers by Friday, February 28, 2020 at noon will receive a Camp T-shirt on the day of camp. There will be NO late orders placed and NO extra shirts will be ordered.

SHS & WHS coaches and players will provide instruction on the following softball skills: Throwing, Fielding, Hitting, Bunting, Baserunning, Pitching and more.

Campers will need to bring a glove and gym shoes. SHS & WHS are not responsible for any lost or stolen items.

Space is limited to 75 campers.

All campers will receive a participation certification.

Door Prizes will be awarded.

Please see the link below for more info and registration form.

https://www.woodland5.net/UserFiles/Servers/Server_24464691/File/News%20Files/Softball%20Camp%20Flyer%202020%20.pdf

When: Saturday March 21, 2020
Where: SHS “Pops” Dale Gym

1 Session Only: Grades 1-8 (9:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.) Check in begins at 8:45 a.m. Participants will be broken into groups based on grade level.

Cost: $25 per camper ($15 per additional sibling)

Each camper that registers by Friday, February 28, 2020 at noon will receive a Camp T-shirt on the day of camp. There will be NO late orders placed and NO extra shirts will be ordered.

SHS & WHS coaches and players will provide instruction on the following softball skills: Throwing, Fielding, Hitting, Bunting, Baserunning, Pitching and more.

Campers will need to bring a glove and gym shoes. SHS & WHS are not responsible for any lost or stolen items.

Space is limited to 75 campers.

All campers will receive a participation certification.

Door Prizes will be awarded.

Please see the link below for more info and registration form.

Woodland is proud to announce the beginning of a band for students in 4th, 5th, and 6th grades.

Band is back at Woodland!

Band will be available for 4th, 5th, and 6th grade students
We will begin meeting after school December 2nd from 3-4:30pm. Rehearsals will be after school to begin. A representative from The Music Shoppe will be coming in to demonstrate and prepare students for instruments. On a later date, students will “try-out” different instruments and receive their chosen instrument in January. For the first three months, the district will cover the rental fees of instruments and instruction materials. If you have any questions please call or email Mr. Levy levya@woodland5.net or 815.672.5974 x:1320
